### RxDB postCreate Hook: Modifying RxDocuments

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/middleware.md

The postCreate hook in RxDB is used to modify RxDocument instances as they are constructed. It allows for the addition of custom getters and setters, providing a flexible way to add specific behavior to documents. This hook must be synchronous.

```javascript
myCollection.postCreate(function(plainData, rxDocument){
    Object.defineProperty(rxDocument, 'myField', {
        get: () => 'foobar',
    });
});

const doc = await myCollection.findOne().exec();

console.log(doc.myField);
// 'foobar'
```

