### Add Custom Getter to RxDocument with postCreate (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/middleware.html

This snippet demonstrates how to use the postCreate hook to add a custom getter named 'myField' to every RxDocument instance in a collection. The getter returns the string 'foobar'. This hook is synchronous and modifies documents as they are constructed.

```javascript
myCollection.postCreate(function(plainData, rxDocument){
    Object.defineProperty(rxDocument, 'myField', {
        get: () => 'foobar'
    });
});

const doc = await myCollection.findOne().exec();
console.log(doc.myField); // 'foobar'
```

